"title": "6242: adultery",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6242: adultery",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Sexual relations involving at least one partner who is married to someone else. Such relations break the marriage covenant and are condemned in Scripture. Jesus Christ extended the understanding of adultery to include inner lust.</p>\n<h2>Adultery is condemned by God</h2>\n<h3>God's law forbids it</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:14\">EXO 20:14</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:18\">DEU 5:18</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:20\">LEV 18:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:18\">MAT 19:18</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:19\">MRK 10:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:20\">LUK 18:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:11\">JAS 2:11</a></p>\n<h3>It is listed with other evil practices</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:18\">PSA 50:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:9-Jer7:10\">JER 7:9–7:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:1-Hos4:2\">HOS 4:1–4:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:11\">LUK 18:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:9-1Tim1:10\">1TI 1:9–1:10</a></p>\n<h2>The lure of adultery</h2>\n<h3>It begins with lust</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:25\">PRO 6:25</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:27-Matt5:28\">MAT 5:27–5:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:2-2Sam11:3\">2SA 11:2–11:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:1\">JOB 31:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:9\">JOB 31:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:8\">JER 5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:19\">MAT 15:19</a></p>\n<h3>It is seductive</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:14-Prov7:21\">PRO 7:14–7:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:3\">PRO 5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:20\">PRO 5:20</a></p>\n<h3>It is secretive</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:15\">JOB 24:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:8-Prov7:10\">PRO 7:8–7:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:20\">PRO 30:20</a></p>\n<h3>It is a snare to the unwary</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:7\">PRO 7:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:14\">PRO 22:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:26\">ECC 7:26</a></p>\n<h3>It is resisted by the wise</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:16\">PRO 2:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:7-Gen39:12\">GEN 39:7–39:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:4-Prov7:5\">PRO 7:4–7:5</a></p>\n<h2>Adultery breaks the marriage covenant</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:17\">PRO 2:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:2\">HOS 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:14\">MAL 2:14</a></p>\n<h2>The consequences of adultery</h2>\n<h3>It destroys individuals and society</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:32-Prov6:34\">PRO 6:32–6:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:4-Prov5:5\">PRO 5:4–5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:9-Prov5:11\">PRO 5:9–5:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:26-Prov6:29\">PRO 6:26–6:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:22-Prov7:27\">PRO 7:22–7:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:11-Job31:12\">JOB 31:11–31:12</a></p>\n<h3>It was punishable by death under OT law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:10\">LEV 20:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:22\">DEU 22:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:23-Deut22:24\">DEU 22:23–22:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:4-John8:5\">JHN 8:4–8:5</a></p>\n<h3>Adulterers face God's judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:4\">HEB 13:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:11-2Sam12:12\">2SA 12:11–12:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:5\">MAL 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:9\">1CO 6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:22\">REV 2:22</a></p>\n<h2>Remarriage after divorce may be adultery</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:9\">MAT 19:9</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:11\">MRK 10:11</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:32\">MAT 5:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:18\">LUK 16:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:3\">ROM 7:3</a></p>\n<h2>Hypocrisy in relation to adultery</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:22\">ROM 2:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:5-2Sam12:6\">2SA 12:5–12:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:14\">HOS 4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:7-John8:9\">JHN 8:7–8:9</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of adultery</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:1-2Sam11:4\">2SA 11:1–11:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:7\">JER 5:7</a> <em>the people of Jerusalem</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer29:23\">JER 29:23</a> <em>the exiles in Babylon</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos3:1-Hos3:3\">HOS 3:1–3:3</a> <em>Hosea's wife, Gomer</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:3\">JHN 8:3</a> <em>the woman caught in adultery</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:14\">2PE 2:14</a> <em>false teachers in the church</em></p>\n<h2>Children born of adultery</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:3\">ISA 57:3</a></strong> <em>“offspring of adulterers” was a term of abuse.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:15-2Sam12:18\">2SA 12:15–12:18</a> <em>David and Bathsheba's child died when he was seven days old</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:4-Hos2:5\">HOS 2:4–2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:7\">HOS 5:7</a></p>",
